'''Marlies ter Borg-Neervoort''' ( born 24 December 1948, [[Palembang|Pladjoe, Palembang]])<ref>[http://www.marliesterborg.net/media/8199/palembang%20revisited.pdf Marlies ter Borg-Neervoort, Palembang ad Pladjoe revisited]</ref> is a Dutch [[Philosophy|philosopher]], editor and author. Her work focuses principally on the study of texts in the [[Bible]] and [[Quran|Qu'ran]]. She is the author of ''Koran en Bijbel in Verhalen'' (''Qu'ran and Bible in Stories'') and ''Sharing Mary: Bible and Qu'ran side by side''. Both works focus on comparative textual analysis in both holy books.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kerknieuws.nl/nieuws.asp?oId=11867&lStrActionReactie=hide|title=Bijbel en Koran lijken in verhalen veel op elkaar|work=Kerknieuws.nl|accessdate=21 July 2010|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trouw.nl/krantenarchief/2007/10/19/2314426/_Bijbel_is_nog_erger_dan_Koran_.html|title=’Bijbel is nog erger dan Koran’|work=[[Trouw]]|accessdate=21 July 2010|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/binnenland/1775624/___Koran_vrouwvriendelijker_dan_gedacht___.html?p=24,2|title='Koran vrouwvriendelijker dan gedacht'|work=[[De Telegraaf]]|accessdate=21 July 2010|language=nl}}</ref>

